This paper deals with formalizing prescriptive obligations and the diagnostic problem of defeasible deontic logic, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses legal reasoning, which falls under the category of computational law (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper touches upon the topic of criminal behavior, which could be categorized under cybersecurity (cs.CR) or cybercrime (cs.CC).
